               <occupation type="political">ruler </occupation>
               
               <floruit notBefore="1751" notAfter="1759">He was the governor of <placeName ref="LOC3549Gojjam">Goǧǧām</placeName> 
                  from <date>1751</date> to <date>1759</date>. His early life history is obscure, but he descended from <persName ref="ETH1126Amhara">ʾAmhārā</persName>, 
                  <persName ref="ETH1973Oromo">Oromo</persName> and <persName ref="ETH1499Gafat">Gāfāt</persName>. 
                  <persName ref="PRS10451Yosedeq">Yosedeq Walda ʾAbib</persName> was in hostile relation with <persName ref="PRS5617IyasuII">ʾIyāsu II</persName>
                  after he demoted his father <persName ref="PRS9873WaldaAb">Walda ʾAbib</persName> in <date>1749</date>,  but later he made peaceful relation through 
                  marriage alliance with the king, marrying the half-sister of <persName ref="PRS5617IyasuII">ʾIyāsu II</persName>, 
                  <persName ref="PRS9827Walatta">Walatta ʾƎsrāʾel</persName> and daughter of <persName ref="PRS2682BerhanM">Bǝrhan Mogasā</persName>. 
                     Then, he was appointed as the governor of <placeName ref="LOC3549Gojjam">Goǧǧām</placeName> in <date>1751</date>. 
                
               
      </floruit>
               
